# Hockey Hub Design System Guidelines

## Standard Context Instructions
- Always use designs from @codebase src/components/examples/HockeyAppUIComponents.tsx for reference
- Use utility constants from @codebase src/lib/design-utils.ts for colors and styles
- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns with Tailwind CSS for all UI elements

## Component Import Standards
- Always import shadcn/ui components from @/components/ui/
- Always import icons from lucide-react
- Import utility functions from @/lib/utils
- Import design constants from @/lib/design-utils

## Style Conventions
- Use Tailwind utility classes instead of custom CSS
- Use the standard color schemes for event types:
  - Ice training: bg-blue-100 text-blue-800
  - Physical training: bg-green-100 text-green-800
  - Game: bg-red-100 text-red-800
  - Rehab/Medical: bg-amber-100 text-amber-800
  - Meetings: bg-purple-100 text-purple-800
  - Travel: bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-800

- Use standard color schemes for player status:
  - Fully available: bg-green-100 text-green-800
  - Limited: bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800
  - Individual training: bg-orange-100 text-orange-800
  - Rehab: bg-red-100 text-red-800
  - Unavailable: bg-gray-100 text-gray-800

## Component Structure
- Follow compound component patterns (Card with CardHeader, CardContent, etc.)
- Implement responsive design with sm:, md:, lg: breakpoint prefixes
- Use consistent spacing (gap-4, space-y-3, p-4)